Hei!\n\nWish on saanut California Propos.source_string:
Hello,

Wish has received a California Proposition 65 notice regarding your product(s) and/or product category(s). A California Proposition 65 violation can constitute a violation of Wish’s Terms of Use (see sec. 5 para. 6) and Wish policies; see, e.g.: Wish Merchant Policy 7.20.

What is Proposition 65?

Proposition 65 is a ballot initiative passed by California voters in 1986, is a toxic chemicals right-to-know law requiring a company doing business in California to place warnings on products and, if the product is sold on the internet, on web pages featuring the product.  The law requires the warning when certain chemicals in the products are present in levels that could cause certain levels of exposure to the consumer. 

The law allows private enforcers to bring notices of violation of any of 950 chemicals it regulates, which in turn requires the company, as one option, to add warnings that the product at issue contains specific chemicals that can cause cancer or reproductive harm.  Another option is to withdraw the product from California sale. Neither option exempts the company from liability for the period of time the product was sold to California consumers without a warning.  The warning must be both on the product packaging and on the Wish web page where the product is featured.

Actions Taken by Wish

In response to this report, Wish has reviewed the applicable listing(s) for non-compliance and the following product listing(s) was removed from the platform in all applicable jurisdictions:

Sorry to hear that! Here's a few things to check that might help you locate that order:
-See if a notice of attempted delivery was left by the carrier
-Double check your shipping address from your Order History to ensure it shipped to the right place
-Check the surrounding area of your mailbox, front door, or back door to see if the package is hidden somewhere safe nearby
-Confirm that someone else didn't accept your package, such as a building manager, neighbor, or household member
-Make sure there are no additional VAT or Customs required to deliver your goods
-Check to see if the carrier delivered your item to a safe, pick up location instead of your delivery address
-Check with your local postal office or the private delivery service office indicated in your order's tracking history

Wishillä asiakas on aina etusijalla, ja.source_string:
At Wish, we put customers first and are willing to pay to insure that Wish users receive excellent service. Today, we learned that one of your orders was not prepared in accordance with Postnord rules, so we have automatically refunded you for your purchase!

Sometimes, merchants have already shipped your package. If this is the case, you may receive a message from Postnord to pay VAT and the handling fee. Since you have already been refunded, you will have two options:

1. If you don't want your item, then do nothing & ignore the messages. OR.
2. If you do want your item, contact Postnord with your order ID and they will release the package free of charge. That means we’ve covered your whole purchase, shipping fees & Postnord VAT for you!

We apologize for any inconvenience and are working round the clock to make sure all 1 million merchants follow Postnord rules in the future!

For UK Customers

Buying products online from businesses that don’t give a UK address increases the risk to consumers. Online platforms are not always the seller of the products on their websites and often act as an intermediary between an independent company and the buyer. If you would like additional information, you can contact the consumer protection agency {%1=link 1}

Yhdistyneen kuningaskunnan nykyinen alle.source_string: Beginning 1 January, 2021 the current VAT exemption for UK imports of goods in a small consignment of value up to £15 will end. As of this date, VAT will be included in your purchase price on items and consignments of up to £135 imported into the UK. This will also mean that you will not have to pay any additional VAT at customs.
